The accused had written to the DPP seeking to have the decision to charge him reviewed.He denied the charge read to him virtually at the Milimani Law Courts. A former legislator has eventually been charged with forging company minutes of the family’s Sh20billion estate in the upmarket Kitsuru area in Nairobi County.
Former Tetu MP, Mr James Ndung’u Gethenji, was charged before Milimani Law Courts Chief Magistrate Ms Martha Mutuku on December 17, 2020.
This even after the accused wrote to the Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP) Noordin Haji on November 30, 2020 seeking to have the decision to charge him reviewed. the decision to charge him.



